{
	"name": "Engulf",
	"type": "feat",
	"img": "icons/magic/water/pseudopod-swirl-blue.webp",
	"system": {
		"description": {
			"value": "<p><em>The [[lookup @name lowercase]] closes with a creature, capable of moving through its space. Whenever it enters a creature's space, the creature must make a <strong>DC 12 Dexterity</strong> saving throw.</em></p><p><strong>[[/save dex]]{Dexterity Save}</strong></p><ul><li><p><strong>Failure:</strong> The [[lookup @name lowercase]] ends its movement in the creature's space, and the creature immediately takes 10 (3d6) acid damage as it is swallowed.</p></li><li><p><strong>Success:</strong> The creature can be pushed 5 feet back or to the side of the [[lookup @name lowercase]]. If it declines the push, it still suffers the effects of a failed save.</p></li></ul><p><strong>Engulfed:</strong> The creature is restrained, can't breathe, and takes 21 (6d6) acid damage at the start of each of the [[lookup @name lowercase]]'s turns. When the [[lookup @name lowercase]] moves, the creature moves with it. The engulfed creature can use an action to make a [[/check]]{Strength check, DC 12}. On a success the creature escapes and appears in a space of its choice within 5 feet of the [[lookup @name lowercase]].</p>",
			"chat": ""
		},
